<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q2_v1" title="Q2_v1" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>¿Cuántos números enteros negativos pertenecen al intervalo [-5, 2]?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        
        4
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Los enteros negativos del intervalo <strong>[-5, 2]</strong> son <strong>-5, -4, -3, -2 y -1</strong>. Al contarlos se obtiene <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>5</mn></math>, no <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>4</mn></math>.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        5
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Los números enteros negativos que pertenecen al intervalo <strong>[-5, 2]</strong> son <strong>-5, -4, -3, -2 y -1</strong>. Hay exactamente <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>5</mn></math> números.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        
        6
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. En el intervalo <strong>[-5, 2]</strong> aparecen los enteros <strong>-5, -4, -3, -2, -1, 0, 1, 2</strong>, pero el problema pide solo los <strong>enteros negativos</strong>. Esos son <strong>-5, -4, -3, -2 y -1</strong>, que suman <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>5</mn></math>, no <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>6</mn></math>.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        
        7
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Los enteros negativos del intervalo <strong>[-5, 2]</strong> son solamente <strong>-5, -4, -3, -2 y -1</strong>. Como <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>5</mn></math> números cumplen la condición, la cantidad no puede ser <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>7</mn></math>.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar el intervalo</strong></p>
            <p>El intervalo es <strong>[-5, 2]</strong>. Como los corchetes indican que los extremos están incluidos, pertenecen al intervalo todos los enteros desde <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>-5</mn></math> hasta <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>2</mn></math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Escribir los enteros del intervalo</strong></p>
            <p>Los enteros que pertenecen a <strong>[-5, 2]</strong> son: <strong>-5, -4, -3, -2, -1, 0, 1, 2</strong>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Seleccionar solo los enteros negativos</strong></p>
            <p>Un entero negativo es menor que <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>0</mn></math>. Por eso, de la lista anterior, los negativos son: <strong>-5, -4, -3, -2 y -1</strong>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Contar cuántos hay</strong></p>
            <p>Contamos los números: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>-5</mn></math>, <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>-4</mn></math>, <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>-3</mn></math>, <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>-2</mn></math> y <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>-1</mn></math>. En total hay <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>5</mn></math> enteros negativos.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La respuesta correcta es <strong>5</strong>, es decir, la alternativa <strong>B</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>